{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Firefox 24 for developers","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/24","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n  <ol>\n    <li class=\"toggle\">\n        <details>\n            <summary>Firefox developer release notes</summary>\n            <ol>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases\">Firefox developer release notes</a></li>\n            </ol>\n        </details>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"toggle\">\n        <details>\n            <summary>Add-ons</summary>\n            <ol>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/Add-ons/WebExtensions\">Browser extensions</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/Add-ons/Themes\">Themes</a></li>\n            </ol>\n        </details>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"toggle\">\n        <details>\n            <summary>Firefox internals</summary>\n            <ol>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/\">Mozilla project</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Gecko\">Gecko</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Headless_mode\">Headless mode</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/JavaScript_code_modules\">JavaScript code modules</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/js-ctypes\">JS-ctypes</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/MathML_Project\">MathML project</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/MFBT\">MFBT</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Projects\">Mozilla projects</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Preferences\">Preference system</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/WebIDL_bindings\">WebIDL bindings</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XPCOM\">XPCOM</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL\">XUL</a></li>\n            </ol>\n        </details>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"toggle\">\n        <details>\n            <summary>Building and contributing</summary>\n            <ol>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Developer_guide/Build_Instructions\">Build instructions</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Developer_guide/Build_Instructions/Configuring_Build_Options\">Configuring build options</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Developer_guide/Build_Instructions/How_Mozilla_s_build_system_works\">How the build system works</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Developer_guide/Source_Code/Mercurial\">Mozilla source code</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Localization\">Localization</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Mercurial\">Mercurial</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/QA\">Quality assurance</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Using_Mozilla_code_in_other_projects\">Using Mozilla code in other projects</a></li>\n            </ol>\n        </details>\n    </li>\n  </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"changes_for_web_developers","title":"Changes for Web developers","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"css","title":"CSS","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>The two values <code>-moz-zoom-in</code> and <code>-moz-zoom-out</code> of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/cursor\"><code>cursor</code></a> property have been unprefixed to <code>zoom-in</code> and <code>zoom-out</code> (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=772153\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;772153</a>).</li>\n  <li>To match the specification, the keywords <code>not</code>, <code>only</code>, <code>and</code>, and <code>or</code> cannot be used as media types anymore (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=757554\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;757554</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"html","title":"HTML","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/track\"><code>&lt;track&gt;</code></a> element has been implemented behind the <code>media.webvtt.enabled</code> preference, and is disabled by default. (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=833385\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;833385</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"javascript","title":"JavaScript","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Functions/Arrow_functions\">Arrow functions</a> are no longer automatically in strict mode unless explicitly requested with <code>\"use strict\"</code> (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=852762\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;852762</a>).</li>\n  <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/repeat\"><code>String.prototype.repeat</code></a> JS method has been implemented (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=815431\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;815431</a>).</li>\n  <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Set/values\"><code>Set.prototype.values()</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Set/values\"><code>Set.prototype.keys()</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Set/entries\"><code>Set.prototype.entries()</code></a> methods on <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Set\"><code>Set</code></a> objects have been implemented (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=869996\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;869996</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"dom","title":"DOM","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>Support for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Range/Range\" title=\"Range()\"><code>Range()</code></a> constructor has been added (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=868999\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;868999</a>).</li>\n  <li>Support for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Text/Text\" title=\"Text()\"><code>Text()</code></a> constructor has been added (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=869000\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;869000</a>).</li>\n  <li>Support for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Comment/Comment\" title=\"Comment()\"><code>Comment()</code></a> constructor has been added (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=869006\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;869006</a>).</li>\n  <li>Support for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DocumentFragment/DocumentFragment\" title=\"DocumentFragment()\"><code>DocumentFragment()</code></a> constructor has been added (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=869002\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;869002</a>).</li>\n  <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FocusEvent\"><code>FocusEvent</code></a> interface has been implemented (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=855741\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;855741</a>).</li>\n  <li>Support for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/remove\"><code>ChildNode.remove()</code></a> method has been added (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=856629\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;856629</a>).</li>\n  <li>The WebVTT interfaces related to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/track\"><code>&lt;track&gt;</code></a> element, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTrackElement\"><code>HTMLTrackElement</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextTrack\"><code>TextTrack</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextTrackCue\"><code>TextTrackCue</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextTrackList\"><code>TextTrackList</code></a>, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextTrackCueList\"><code>TextTrackCueList</code></a> have been implemented behind the <code>media.webvtt.enabled</code> property, defaulting to <code>false</code> (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=833385\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;833385</a>).</li>\n  <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gamepad\"><code>Gamepad</code></a> interface, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getGamepads\"><code>Navigator.getGamepads</code></a> have been implemented behind the <code>dom.gamepad.enabled</code> property, defaulting to <code>false</code> (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=690935\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;690935</a>).</li>\n  <li>On desktop Firefox only, <code>HTMLCanvasElement.getContext()</code> can now take the <code>webgl</code> value, in addition to <code>experimental-webgl</code> (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=870232\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;870232</a>).</li>\n  <li>The non-standard method <code>mozLoadFrom()</code> of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLMediaElement\"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> has been removed (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=877135\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;877135</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"developer_tools","title":"Developer Tools","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>The Network inspector now lets you filter by content type (CSS/image/font etc.) and see the relevant size and load times.</li>\n  <li>The Devtools options panel to the left lets you disable/enable JavaScript temporarily.</li>\n  <li>Extension developers may use the new <a href=\"https://mihai.sucan.ro/mihai/blog/the-browser-console-is-replacing-the-error-console\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Browser Console</a> for Chrome-level scripts (Replaces Error Console).</li>\n  <li>The source map syntax has been changed to use <code>//#</code> instead of <code>//@</code> (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=870361\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;870361</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"mathml","title":"MathML","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>The <code>dir</code> attribute for controlling directionality of formulas on e.g. <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/math\" title=\"<math>\">&lt;math&gt;</a></code> or <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mrow\" title=\"<mrow>\">&lt;mrow&gt;</a></code> elements is now equivalent to using the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/direction\"><code>direction</code></a> CSS property.</li>\n  <li>The equal sign (\"=\") is now <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo#attr-stretchy\">stretchable</a>.</li>\n  <li>The \"<code>updiagonalarrow</code>\" value for the <code>notation</code> attribute on <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/menclose\" title=\"<menclose>\">&lt;menclose&gt;</a></code> elements has been added.</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"changes_for_add-on_and_mozilla_developers","title":"Changes for add-on and Mozilla developers","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>Doc Shells have now the <code>allowMedia</code> attribute to disable media playing (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=759964\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;759964</a>).</li>\n  <li>Sherlock search plugins in the application directory or profile won't be loaded anymore (<a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=862143\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">bug&nbsp;862143</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://website-archive.mozilla.org/www.mozilla.org/firefox_releasenotes/en-us/firefox/24.0a2/auroranotes/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Firefox 24 Aurora Notes</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"older_versions","title":"Older versions","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"multiColumnList\" id=\"sect1\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/23\">Firefox 23 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/22\">Firefox 22 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/21\">Firefox 21 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/20\">Firefox 20 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/19\">Firefox 19 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/18\">Firefox 18 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/17\">Firefox 17 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/16\">Firefox 16 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/15\">Firefox 15 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/14\">Firefox 14 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/13\">Firefox 13 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/12\">Firefox 12 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/11\">Firefox 11 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/10\">Firefox 10 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/9\">Firefox 9 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/8\">Firefox 8 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/7\">Firefox 7 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/6\">Firefox 6 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/5\">Firefox 5 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/4\">Firefox 4 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/3.6\">Firefox 3.6 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/3.5\">Firefox 3.5 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/3\">Firefox 3 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/2\">Firefox 2 for developers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/1.5\">Firefox 1.5 for developers</a></li></ul>\n</div>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Changes for Web developers","id":"changes_for_web_developers"},{"text":"Changes for add-on and Mozilla developers","id":"changes_for_add-on_and_mozilla_developers"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"},{"text":"Older versions","id":"older_versions"}],"summary":"","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:03:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Firefox 24 pour les développeurs","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Firefox 24 for developers","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Firefox 24 for developers","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/mozilla/firefox/releases/24","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/mozilla/firefox/releases/24/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/1ee49b729dc4cd02b862d910f279861f4b30e704","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Mozilla","title":"Mozilla"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox","title":"Firefox"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases","title":"Firefox release notes for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/24","title":"Firefox 24 for developers"}],"pageTitle":"Firefox 24 for developers - Mozilla | MDN","noIndexing":false}}